The reinforcement mechanism of the composites is dominated by precipitation and fine-grained strengthening effect. The good ductility of MoNbRe 0.5 W(TaC) 0.5 composite is contributed to the grain refinement of the BCC matrix phase.
For the base alloy MoNbRe 0.5 W, the yield strength, compressive strength and fracture strain are 896 MPa, 1232 MPa and 7.08 %, respectively.

The T0.6 composite has the maximum yield strength of 1241 MPa and the maximum compressive strength of 2351 MPa. The fracture strain increases when the TaC addition increases from 0 to 0.5, but it decreases with further increase of TaC.
